DIV2.P:
Mrs. N—admires what people wonder at so much;
and says she is just so herself. The Duchess of S—is
of the same opinion.

I gave your service to Mr. Wycherley yesterday;
and desire you to give mine to—let me see—Mr.
Tydcombe.

I must add another Apophthegm of the same noble Earl; it was the saying of a politick prince, “Time and he would get the better of any two others.” To which Lord Oxford made this answer;
“Time and I 'gainst any two?
Chance and I 'gainst Time and you.”

SP.P:
As yet I find I am undiscover'd by Plotwell;
neither is his intrigue in such forwardness as mine,
though he made a fair push for it before me.

Harkee, old put; I came to take your advice,
and not that French son of a whore's scarifications;
and so plague take you both.

Gentlemen, wonder at nothing within these walls;
for ever since I was married, nothing has happen'd
to me in the common course of human life.
